    <item>
      <title>The Greed of Kubera</title>
      <description>Today&apos;s story will change how you see everything... In the mythical kingdom of Lanka, Kubera, the wealthy and powerful god of prosperity, ruled over an empire of gold and precious jewels. He was known for his unmatched generosity, but also for his insatiable hunger for wealth and power. His palace was a labyrinth of treasure and riches, where the floors shone like polished gold and the ceilings were studded with precious gems. Kubera&apos;s treasury was the envy of the gods themselves, and he spent his days accumulating more wealth and treasures. But as Kubera&apos;s greed grew, so did his detachment from the world around him. He became isolated, surrounded by his treasures and his minions, losing touch with the world and its people. His subjects suffered, forced to toil and labor to feed his insatiable appetite for wealth. His family and friends grew distant, tired of his constant pursuit of riches. And yet, Kubera couldn&apos;t stop. His greed consumed him, driving him to accumulate more and more, until he became a shadow of his former self. This is Greed — the insatiable hunger for wealth and material possessions. Today, we chase money, status, and power — ask yourself, what are you accumulating?</description>
